beer.beer_description:
The Lightest One is a 5.0% ABV German-Style Helles Lager. Helles, German for bright, is a crisp, clean, German lager with a touch of hops. For more information on the style, check out the German Beer Institute.

Not only do we love flavorful, easy drinking lagers like this - but now when anyone comes to the brewery and asks us for "our lightest beer" we have a quick answer. So, whether you're new to craft beer and are used to beers on the lighter side, or you are just looking for a full-flavored light and refreshing beer, this beer is for you!

beer.beer_description:
Lagertha Pilsner is named after our brewery - which is named after a Viking shieldmaiden. The name was bestowed upon this beer because this was our first flawless brew day.

Brewed with German Pilsner malt and Saaz & Mosaic hops - this clean crisp and refreshing lager is one of our favorites!
